    <item>
      <title>How to extract folders with history with git</title>
      <link>https://l-lin.github.io/post/2018-02-08-git_extract_folders_with_history/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 08 Feb 2018 10:42:13 +0100</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://l-lin.github.io/post/2018-02-08-git_extract_folders_with_history/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Sometimes at the end of life of a project, one of its sub-project will fly on its own and will have its own lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, you will need to extract the folder of the sub-project.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will a simple copy/paste work? Not so fast, because we will lose the git history of the sub-project.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Git is an awesome tool which has a &amp;ldquo;magical&amp;rdquo; command.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
